
This directory supports user-defined applications.  The 'dummy' directory
contains a Makefile that can be imported into a user-specific application
directory.  To setup an application directory 'app', do the following:

  mkdir app
  cd app
  ln -s ../dummy/.deps .
  ln -s ../dummy/Makefile.am .

The first line of the Makefile in the 'app' directory should have the line:

  include ../dummy/Makefile

Subsequent lines in this file can contain whatever build targets are 
desirable for the Acro-related executable that you wish to build.

This use of the acro/user/dummy/Makefile file enables a user to quickly
setup an application and link the application code with the current Acro
libraries.  In particular, the user can transparently utilize the 
Acro configuration (compiler, flags, etc) when building their application.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
NOTE: this reuse of the acro/user/dummy/Makefile is somewhat experimental.
This is _not_ a typical use of an autoconf-generated Makefile.  Further,
this requires the availability of the autoconf/automake utilities.  These 
get called during the invocation of 'make' from an application directory!
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
